Two businessmen were yesterday charged in a Nairobi court with obtaining Sh48.4 million from a private company using forged tender documents allegedly signed by Transport PS Paul Maringa Mwangi. David Ambuku and Paul Owiti are also facing another charge of forging tender documents for supply of 2,830 oil treated angling tail lines purporting to have been genuine tender. The court heard that on or about January 16, atTranscom House the accused forged document purporting to be signed by PS Paul Mwangi. The magistrate ordered each be released on Sh3 million bond or a cash bail of Sh2 million.